---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import ConceptNotice from '../components/ConceptNotice.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy — DripNow" description="How DripNow collects and uses data on this pre-launch waitlist site.">
  <Nav />
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-24">
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink/60">Last updated: [PLACEHOLDER — insert date]</p>

    <div class="mt-8">
      <ConceptNotice />
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-10 text-ink/80 leading-relaxed">
      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-ink">1. Who we are</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          DripNow ("we", "us") operates this website.
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
          <li>Company name: [PLACEHOLDER]</li>
          <li>Registration number (KvK): [PLACEHOLDER]</li>
          <li>Registered address: [PLACEHOLDER]</li>
          <li>Contact: <a class="underline hover:text-ink" href="mailto:hello@dripnow.me">hello@dripnow.me</a></li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-ink">2. What this website currently does</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Right now, dripnow.me is a pre-launch waitlist page with an interactive
          demo. It does not yet offer the full DripNow service (uploading real
          outfit photos and receiving a personalised lookbook). This policy
          explains what we collect today, and what we promise for the future
          service described below.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-ink">3. What data we collect</h2>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
          <li>Your email address, submitted voluntarily via our waitlist form (hosted by Tally).</li>
          <li>UTM parameters (e.g. utm_source, utm_medium, utm_campaign) captured when you land on the page, so we know which channel referred you. These are stored together with your email if you sign up; they are not linked to any other identifier.</li>
          <li>We do not create accounts, use passwords, or collect payment details on this site.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-ink">4. The interactive demo does not use your photos</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The "Try the demo" section on this page runs entirely in your browser
          using fixed sample data. It does not ask for, upload, analyse, or
          store any photo of you. No camera or file upload is used anywhere on
          this current site.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-ink">5. Legal basis for processing</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We process your email address and UTM data on the basis of your{' '}
          <strong class="font-semibold text-ink">consent</strong> (Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR),
          given when you submit the waitlist form. You can withdraw this
          consent at any time by unsubscribing or by emailing{' '}
          <a class="underline hover:text-ink" href="mailto:hello@dripnow.me">hello@dripnow.me</a> —
          this does not affect the lawfulness of processing before withdrawal.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-ink">6. How long we keep your data</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We keep your waitlist entry for as long as you remain on the
          waitlist, and delete it within 30 days of you unsubscribing or
          asking us to remove it. If we launch the full product and you
          convert into a user, retention will be governed by the future
          product's own privacy policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-ink">7. Our promise for the future app (not yet live)</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The full DripNow product will ask you to upload outfit photos so our
          AI can build your Drip Profile. When that feature goes live:
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 rounded-lg border border-ink/15 bg-bone px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink">
          Photos are analysed to build your profile and then deleted —
          never stored or shared.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We are publishing this commitment now so it is in place before that
          feature launches.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-ink">8. Who processes data on our behalf</h2>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
          <li>Tally (tally.so) — hosts and stores waitlist form submissions.</li>
          <li>Porkbun — hosts this static website.</li>
          <li>[PLACEHOLDER — add analytics provider here if/when one is enabled, e.g. Plausible or GA4]</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-ink">9. International data transfers</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Some of our processors (e.g. Tally, Porkbun) may store or process
          data outside the European Economic Area.{' '}
          <span class="font-semibold">
            [PLACEHOLDER — verify safeguards per processor: confirm whether
            Tally/Porkbun rely on Standard Contractual Clauses, an adequacy
            decision, or another Art. 46 GDPR safeguard, and reference the
            specific mechanism here before launch.]
          </span>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-ink">10. Affiliate disclosure</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          DripNow earns a commission on items purchased through links in our
          (future) lookbooks, at no extra cost to you. This does not affect
          the data described in this policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-ink">11. Your rights</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">You have the right to:</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
          <li>access the data we hold about you;</li>
          <li>correct inaccurate data;</li>
          <li>request deletion;</li>
          <li>restrict or object to processing; and</li>
          <li>data portability.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          You also have the right to lodge a complaint with your national data
          protection authority — in the Netherlands, the
          Autoriteit Persoonsgegevens. To exercise any of these rights, email{' '}
          <a class="underline hover:text-ink" href="mailto:hello@dripnow.me">hello@dripnow.me</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-ink">12. Cookies</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          This site uses a cookie-consent banner. We only load non-essential
          cookies (such as analytics) after you give consent. See the banner
          on first visit for details of what, if anything, is currently
          active.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-ink">13. Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We may update this policy as the product develops. Material changes
          will be reflected in the "Last updated" date above.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-ink">14. Contact</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Questions about this policy:{' '}
          <a class="underline hover:text-ink" href="mailto:hello@dripnow.me">hello@dripnow.me</a>
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
